AB  - In this paper we show that the Carter-Nagar (1977) R2's for single structural equations and systems are in fact R2 for the reduced form where the partially restricted reduced form estimation method is employed. We also show that the results of McElroy (1977) may be used to derive the Carter-Nagar system measure. If the reduced form equations are estimated by Kakwani's (1975) k-class reduced form estimator a new R2 may be defined which is shown to be asymptotically equivalent to the Carter-Nagar measure.
