AB  - This comment presents a generalised derivation of the maximum likelihood estimator of the parameters in a simultaneous equation model which incorporates an important class of models not included in Hendry (1976), namely those which have singular error covariance matrices. In so doing it conveniently brings under the scope of Hendry's analysis those models associated with systems of demand equations, models with identities and the joint structural and reduced form formulations proposed by Court (1974).
